rComments: Surprisingly one of the most enjoyable courses. You pick your own topic so you are literally deciding what you want to study for the course. Professor Riendeau is an essay-writing wizard and will gladly provide critique and help you perfect your paper. You get to re-submit work as many times as you want until you are satisfied with the grade.
He comes off as incredibly arrogant, but one-on-one he actually just wants you to succeed (and thinks he has the best way to do it).
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader']

rComments: Very easy class. If you want to learn about JFK it is great, but I didn't learn a damn thing about "critical thinking & inquiry" all semester... more like JFK101 than INI304

Course focuses more on PROCESS than CONTENT. Nothing to read or memorize for exam. I TOTALLY LOVED THE COURSE, cause I could tailor material acc. 2 my interest! A year course with only 2 essays. Yet PRICELESS experince, cause Riendeau teaches you to write an essay line-by-line. Very enthusiastic prof. But moves from side-2-side which made me dizzy!
He talks so slow and monotonously! I dropped this course solely because I couldnt bear to hear him talk.
JFK- THis course was very interesting, the setup is well done, but prof?&#63
